                        <summary>
                            <bibl><ptr target="bib:GopinathaRao1988_01"/></bibl>:
                            <quote>This single verse is also engraved on the door-post on the south side of the <foreign>gopura</foreign>, and
                                records the date of the coronation of Aḻakaṉ Civala-vēḷ. It took place on Monday, the 20th of
                                Cittirai of the year Raktākṣi, Śaka 1486. This day corresponded with the 6th <foreign>tithi</foreign> of the
                                bright half of that month, the <foreign>nakṣatra</foreign> being Punarvasu. The king is the well known
                                Ativīrarāma Pāṇḍya of literary fame.</quote>
                        </summary>
