            <div type="translation" source="bib:GopinathaRao1988_01">      
                
                <p>Aḻakaṉ who revels in perfumes etc., wore the crown in the presence, of all the people
                    under the name of Civalavēḷ, on the first day of the week, the sixth <foreign>tithi</foreign> of the first fortnight
                    and the twentieth of the month of Cittirai, in the year Raktākṣin corresponding to the Śaka
                    year one thousand four hundred and eighty-six.</p>
            </div>
            
